	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />This is a fairly typical 8x8 pixel font for the "codepage 437" character encoding. I don't think <a href="http://pics.pineight.com/nes/8x8s.png" class="postlink">bitmap fonts like these</a> are <a href="http://nwalsh.com/comp.fonts/FAQ/cf_13.htm" class="postlink">copyrightable in the United States</a>, as they are more "useful" than "works of authorship". This means that a font might be subject to a design patent (which you have to pay to apply for), not a copyright (which is automatic in all WTO member states). So there's no copyright violation.
<br />
<br />But I have edited out the hex dump because it's redundant: anyone can reproduce it with Grit from devkitARM.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


